{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {META_DATA}: THE CURIOUS CASE OF BENJAMIN BUTTON
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {META_DATA}: Written by
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {META_DATA}: Eric Roth
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {META_DATA}: Based on the short story by F. Scott Fitzgerald
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {META_DATA}: 10/30/07
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As all things do, it begins in the dark.
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: EYES blink open.
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blue eyes.
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The first thing they see is a WOMAN near 40, standing looking out a window, watching the wind blowing, rattling a window.
{0:0:0 - 0:0:43} {CHARACTER_NAME}: A WOMAN'S (V.O.)
{0:0:40 - 0:0:43} {DIALOGUE}: What are you looking at?
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {DIALOGUE}: The wind, Mother... They say a hurricane is on its way... You've been asleep... I was waiting to see you...
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 1 INT. HOSPITAL ROOM, NEW ORLEANS - MORNING, PRESENT
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now we see we're in a hospital room with layers of white enamel paint trying without success to hide the years... An old WOMAN, past 80, withered, still regal with a green turban around her bald head is propped by pillows, her blue eyes looking out at us from her bed... She's connected to an intravenous for sustenance and a morphine drip... Her name, is DAISY FULLER.
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She speaks with a Southern lilt.
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {CHARACTER_NAME}: DAISY
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {DIALOGUE}: If it wasn't for hurricanes we wouldn't have a hurricane season.
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {DIALOGUE}: I've forgotten what the weather can be like here.
{0:0:40 - 0:1:3} {DIALOGUE}: I've lived with four seasons so many years now.
