{0:7:38 - 0:7:41} {DIALOGUE}: "This is my last will and testament...
{0:7:38 - 0:7:45} {META_DATA}: (which starts to engage her)
{0:7:41 - 0:7:45} {DIALOGUE}: I don't have much to leave... few possessions, no money really... I will go out of this world the same way I came in, alone and with nothing.
{0:7:41 - 0:7:57} {META_DATA}: (finding herself engaged)
{0:7:53 - 0:7:57} {DIALOGUE}: All I have is my story... I'm writing it now while I still remember it..."
{0:7:53 - 0:8:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's interested.
{0:7:53 - 0:8:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks over at her mother.
{0:7:53 - 0:8:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But her mother's eyes are closed...
{0:7:53 - 0:8:1} {CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE (CONT'D)
{0:7:57 - 0:8:1} {DIALOGUE}: "My name is Benjamin..."
{0:7:57 - 0:8:4} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And Caroline's voice becomes a young MAN'S voice...
{0:7:57 - 0:8:4} {CHARACTER_NAME}: A MAN'S (V.O.)
{0:8:1 - 0:8:4} {DIALOGUE}: "Benjamin Button... and I was born under unusual circumstances."
{0:8:1 - 0:8:7} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 19 EXT. NEW ORLEANS - NIGHT 1918
{0:8:1 - 0:8:7} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THERE'S SUDDENLY AN EXPLOSION OF FIREWORKS.
