{0:9:4 - 0:9:5} {DIALOGUE}: Promise me, Thomas...
{0:9:4 - 0:9:8} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And she is interrupted by the sudden CRY OF A BABY.
{0:9:4 - 0:9:8} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But Thomas can't take his eyes from his dying wife...
{0:9:4 - 0:9:8} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HIS YOUNG WIFE (CONT'D)
{0:9:6 - 0:9:8} {DIALOGUE}: Promise me, he has a place...
{0:9:6 - 0:9:19} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't understand... She looks up at him... holds his hand tight... then she slips away... The Doctor listening for her pulse... He covers her... it's quiet... the Priest's murmured incantations... the housemaids crying...
{0:9:6 - 0:9:19} {META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{0:9:6 - 0:9:19} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 11.
{0:9:6 - 0:9:19} {META_DATA}: 21 CONTINUED:
{0:9:6 - 0:9:19} {CHARACTER_NAME}: BENJAMIN BUTTON'S (V.O.)
{0:9:16 - 0:9:19} {DIALOGUE}: She gave her life for me... And for that I am forever grateful...
{0:9:16 - 0:9:30} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Thomas, still holding her hand, is unable to let go... When we hear again the BABY CRYING... The BABY'S CRY is not quite right... It is not an infant's cry for succor, or a natural cry to exercise its new lungs... It's a deep, haunting cry from some primal soul... They all turn, and the room stills... listening as The BABY continues its mournful WAIL.
{0:9:16 - 0:9:30} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Only Thomas goes to answer... The Baby in a basket, swaddled in a thick blanket, its face covered with cloth... Thomas goes to lift it, to see his son's face...
{0:9:16 - 0:9:30} {CHARACTER_NAME}: MAID
{0:9:29 - 0:9:30} {DIALOGUE}: Mr. Button...!
{0:9:29 - 0:10:23} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lifts the cloth anyway... He recoils... for he has seen some kind of horror... He makes the smallest of sounds, a whispered "Ohhhh."
{0:9:29 - 0:10:23} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then he suddenly snatches up the swaddled baby -- running with it out of the room... downstairs... outside...
{0:9:29 - 0:10:23} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 22 EXT. NEW ORLEANS - NIGHT, 1918
{0:9:29 - 0:10:23} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ... Thomas, tears on his face, carrying his CRYING BABY, through the streets... Pushing through crowds...
{0:9:29 - 0:10:23} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 23 EXT. A BRIDGE, NEW ORLEANS - NIGHT, 1918
{0:9:29 - 0:10:23} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ... he comes along an old bridge over a waterway... the air heavy with the haze of fireworks... the water dark... brokenhearted, he lifts the baby to throw it into the black water... He is just at the apex of this throw when, despite his sadness, he can't bring himself to do it... Instead, cradles the newborn...
{0:9:29 - 0:10:23} {CHARACTER_NAME}: THOMAS
{0:9:29 - 0:10:23} {DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry... I'm so sorry...
