{0:21:57 - 0:22:0} {DIALOGUE}: "Kind keepers of my weak decaying age, Let dying Mortimer here rest himself.
{0:22:6 - 0:22:8} {DIALOGUE}: Even like a man new haled from the rack.
{0:22:8 - 0:22:11} {DIALOGUE}: So fare my limbs with long imprisonment.
{0:22:12 - 0:22:16} {DIALOGUE}: And these gray locks, the pursuivants of death, Nestor-like aged in an age of care, Argue the end of Edmund Mortimer."
{0:22:12 - 0:22:26} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Benjamin's mouth agape, awed, taken by him, his majesty.
