{0:29:39 - 0:29:58} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks out...
{0:29:39 - 0:29:58} {CHARACTER_NAME}: NGUNDA OTI (CONT'D)
{0:29:55 - 0:29:58} {DIALOGUE}: I think about the river I grew up on.
{0:29:58 - 0:30:1} {DIALOGUE}: It would be good to sit by my river again.
{0:29:58 - 0:30:10} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at his watch.
{0:29:58 - 0:30:10} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He suddenly gets up...
{0:29:58 - 0:30:10} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 34A.
{0:29:58 - 0:30:10} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 52 EXT. BOURBON STREET CORNER, NEW ORLEANS - DUSK, 1927
{0:29:58 - 0:30:10} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Oti and Benjamin coming along the street, music pouring out... They reach a corner where a tall octoroon woman is waiting.
