{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Snow covers the street outside of a turn-of-the Century hotel... a front window looks into its lobby... "The Winter Palace Hotel."
{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 113 INT. "WINTER PALACE," RUSSIA - NIGHT, 1941
{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a packed BAR off the lobby... We see Benjamin sitting with Captain Mike, their crew, and a mixture of other seamen, Russians and other ethnics, all speaking different languages, sitting and standing around tables cluttered with bottles and glasses... Captain Mike, drunk, his shirt off, is telling a Russian sailor, another interpreting for him -- about a tattoo he has over his heart... an upside down hummingbird...
{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {CHARACTER_NAME}: CAPT. MIKE
{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {DIALOGUE}: I saws this tattoo puts on a man's back in Singapore by Sakumoro, the greatest tattoo artist ever lived.
{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {DIALOGUE}: I puts it on myself from mem'ry.
{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And now we know why it's upside down...
{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {CHARACTER_NAME}: CAPT. MIKE (CONT'D)
{0:59:50 - 1:0:5} {DIALOGUE}: This idn't just anoter bird!
{1:0:2 - 1:0:5} {DIALOGUE}: Its heart rate's twelve hunerd beats a minute...!
{1:0:7 - 1:0:10} {DIALOGUE}: Its wings beats eighty times a second...!
{1:0:7 - 1:0:32} {DIALOGUE}: If you was to stop their wings from beatin, they would be dyin' in less than ten seconds...This is no ordinary bird, this is a frikkin' miracle!
{1:0:28 - 1:0:32} {DIALOGUE}: They slowed down the wings
{1:0:28 - 1:0:46} {META_DATA}: (MORE)
{1:0:28 - 1:0:46} {META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{1:0:28 - 1:0:46} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 75.
