{1:38:9 - 1:38:33} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Benjamin hasn't moved.
{1:38:9 - 1:38:33} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The words ring in his ears.
{1:38:9 - 1:38:33} {CHARACTER_NAME}: THOMAS BUTTON (CONT'D)
{1:38:30 - 1:38:33} {DIALOGUE}: You were born the night the great war ended... Your mother died giving birth to you... I thought... I thought you were a monster... I left you on the back steps of a house... I promised your mother I'd make sure you were safe... I should never have abandoned you...
{1:38:30 - 1:38:48} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Benjamin's dead quiet... He looks at this man, his father...
{1:38:30 - 1:38:48} {CHARACTER_NAME}: BENJAMIN
