{1:38:49 - 1:38:52} {DIALOGUE}: Your grandfather at the summer house on Lake Pontchartrain.
{1:38:55 - 1:38:59} {DIALOGUE}: When I was a boy I would love to wake up before anybody else and run down to the lake to watch the day begin.
{1:39:0 - 1:39:3} {DIALOGUE}: It was as if I was the only one alive.
{1:39:0 - 1:39:7} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And they've come to a young Woman's photograph... who could only be Benjamin's mother.
{1:39:0 - 1:39:7} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops...
{1:39:0 - 1:39:7} {CHARACTER_NAME}: THOMAS BUTTON (CONT'D)
{1:39:5 - 1:39:7} {DIALOGUE}: I fell in love with her the first time I saw her.
{1:39:5 - 1:39:11} {META_DATA}: (beat)
{1:39:8 - 1:39:11} {DIALOGUE}: Your mother's name was Caroline Murphy.
{1:39:8 - 1:39:14} {DIALOGUE}: She was 20.
{1:39:11 - 1:39:14} {DIALOGUE}: She worked in your grandfather's kitchen...She was from Dublin... Her father, your maternal grandfather, was a chimney sweep... He died in the flu epidemic of 1900... Caroline came with her mother, two sisters, and four brothers in 1903 to live in New Orleans.
{1:39:11 - 1:39:44} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They stop at the kitchen door.
{1:39:11 - 1:39:44} {CHARACTER_NAME}: THOMAS BUTTON (CONT'D)
{1:39:11 - 1:39:44} {DIALOGUE}: I would find reasons to go to the kitchen... just to look at her...
{1:39:11 - 1:39:44} {META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{1:39:11 - 1:39:44} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 116.
{1:39:11 - 1:39:44} {META_DATA}: 169 CONTINUED:
{1:39:11 - 1:39:44} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He does just that... Looking through the round window into the empty kitchen... as if she was there those years ago... as if she was still there...
{1:39:11 - 1:39:44} {CHARACTER_NAME}: THOMAS BUTTON (CONT'D)
{1:39:40 - 1:39:44} {DIALOGUE}: The happiest day of my life was April 25th, 1918 the day I married your mother.
{1:39:40 - 1:39:51} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They move along the hallway... Benjamin looking at the photographs... his bloodlines... After some moments:
{1:39:40 - 1:39:51} {CHARACTER_NAME}: BENJAMIN
{1:39:48 - 1:39:51} {DIALOGUE}: Why didn't you tell me?
