{1:39:48 - 1:39:54} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When Benjamin doesn't say anything...
{1:39:48 - 1:39:54} {CHARACTER_NAME}: THOMAS BUTTON (CONT'D)
{1:39:48 - 1:39:54} {DIALOGUE}: We can catch up for all the lost time...
{1:39:48 - 1:39:54} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And when he still doesn't answer...
{1:39:48 - 1:39:54} {CHARACTER_NAME}: THOMAS BUTTON (CONT'D)
{1:39:51 - 1:39:54} {DIALOGUE}: I'm planning on leaving everything I have to you...
{1:39:51 - 1:39:58} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His "bribe" strikes a nerve.
{1:39:51 - 1:39:58} {CHARACTER_NAME}: BENJAMIN
{1:39:51 - 1:39:58} {DIALOGUE}: I better go.
{1:39:51 - 1:39:58} {CHARACTER_NAME}: THOMAS BUTTON
{1:39:56 - 1:39:58} {DIALOGUE}: Where are you going?
{1:39:56 - 1:40:1} {CHARACTER_NAME}: BENJAMIN
{1:39:59 - 1:40:1} {DIALOGUE}: Home.
{1:39:59 - 1:40:3} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Benjamin turns his back and walks out.
{1:39:59 - 1:40:3} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 117.
{1:39:59 - 1:40:3} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 170 INT. QUEENIE'S ROOM - NIGHT, 1946
{1:39:59 - 1:40:3} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Benjamin standing by the door, Queenie sitting up in her bed...
{1:39:59 - 1:40:3} {CHARACTER_NAME}: QUEENIE
{1:39:59 - 1:40:3} {META_DATA}: (unforgiving, angrily)
{1:40:1 - 1:40:3} {DIALOGUE}: He's what?!
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {DIALOGUE}: All those years he's creeping around here, and never tells us who he is?!!
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {DIALOGUE}: I thought he was just queer or somethin' comin' around here... always askin' for you... He left us $18 that night you was found... Eighteen ratty ass dollars and a dirty diaper...!
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {DIALOGUE}: Now he wants to be your father?
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {DIALOGUE}: He wants you to sit at his side...!
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {DIALOGUE}: He wants your forgiveness!
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {DIALOGUE}: I won't ever forgive him for any of it... God's the only one that can forgive him!
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {META_DATA}: (finished)
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {DIALOGUE}: Now I got to get up early with Mrs. Hamilton... or she gonna drown...
{1:40:1 - 1:40:4} {META_DATA}: (but not finished)
{1:40:3 - 1:40:4} {DIALOGUE}: ...He thinks he can just show up, and everything gonna be fine and dandy, everybody gonna be friends... He got another thing coming...
{1:40:3 - 1:40:42} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And with that she turns over, to go back to sleep, Benjamin quietly leaves the room.
{1:40:3 - 1:40:42} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 171 INT. THE NOLAN HOUSE - BACK STAIRS, HALLWAY - NIGHT
{1:40:3 - 1:40:42} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He climbs the back stairs to his room, as if he's carrying a terrible burden... as he comes onto the hallway, Mr. Daws is sitting on a bench in the hall... Seeing Benjamin...
{1:40:3 - 1:40:42} {CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. DAWS
{1:40:38 - 1:40:42} {DIALOGUE}: Did I ever tell you I was struck by lightning seven different times.
{1:40:44 - 1:40:46} {DIALOGUE}: Once, I was walking my dog along a country road.
{1:40:44 - 1:41:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And we see just that, when suddenly he's struck by lightning.
{1:40:44 - 1:41:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dog, unharmed, licking his face.
{1:40:44 - 1:41:1} {META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{1:40:44 - 1:41:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 118.
{1:40:44 - 1:41:1} {META_DATA}: 171 CONTINUED:
{1:40:44 - 1:41:1} {CHARACTER_NAME}: MR. DAWS (CONT'D)
{1:40:56 - 1:41:1} {DIALOGUE}: I'm blind in the one eye...I can't hardly hear...I get twitches and shakes out of nowhere... I lose my line of thought... but you know what... God, for some reason, keeps on sending me a wake-up... It's His way of reminding me I'm lucky to be alive...
{1:40:56 - 1:41:15} {META_DATA}: (a beat, sniffs the air)
{1:41:14 - 1:41:15} {DIALOGUE}: Storm's comin'.
{1:41:14 - 1:41:47} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And gets up and pads off into his room.
{1:41:14 - 1:41:47} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Benjamin, left in the hallway...He goes over to look out the window, like the boy we remember looking out at the street lights... the street...
