{1:50:1 - 1:50:18} {META_DATA}: 186 CONTINUED:
{1:50:1 - 1:50:18} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns to go... she's motionless, caught between the two worlds... And we expect her to yell after him, to stop him... But instead, she does what we all do in these moments, what feels good at the time... She runs to be with her friends... She gets into a taxi... The cab drives by him as they leave... Daisy turned to look out the back window... looking back at him... He waves... letting her go... And another chance for them is missed... The street's quiet.
{1:50:1 - 1:50:18} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And hands in his pockets, a middle-aged man going on 26... he walks off into the night...
{1:50:1 - 1:50:18} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 187 INT. HOSPITAL ROOM, NEW ORLEANS - MORNING, PRESENT
