{1:50:19 - 1:50:26} {DIALOGUE}: You couldn't have known.
{1:50:19 - 1:50:26} {CHARACTER_NAME}: DAISY
{1:50:19 - 1:50:26} {DIALOGUE}: I was 23...I just didn't care...
{1:50:19 - 1:50:37} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's quiet with her thoughts... and, remembering, she hums to herself some distant memory of music...
{1:50:19 - 1:50:37} {CHARACTER_NAME}: DAISY (CONT'D)
{1:50:30 - 1:50:37} {DIALOGUE}: ...There are some photographs I think... the zipper part of the large bag...
{1:50:30 - 1:51:14} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline goes to the suitcases... she comes back with a manila envelope... Daisy dumps them out...and we see they're photographs of Daisy dancing at the height of her abilities...
{1:50:30 - 1:51:14} {CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{1:50:30 - 1:51:14} {DIALOGUE}: I've never seen these... You never talked about your dancing very much...
{1:50:30 - 1:51:14} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Daisy looks at the photographs...
{1:50:30 - 1:51:14} {CHARACTER_NAME}: DAISY
